      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2021-03-09</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-04-15T21:38:35Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><b>Inventor Diversity for Economic Advancement Act of 2021 or the IDEA Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) to request&nbsp;demographic information from the inventor on each patent application submitted to the USPTO.</p> <p>Inventors shall not be required to provide the requested information, which shall include gender, race, and military or veteran status.</p> <p>The USPTO shall (1) publish an annual public report about the collected data, including the collected data broken down by the types of technology covered by the patent applications; and (2) make the underlying data publicly available. </p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-03-09T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
